ate the world model. Helpful optional prefixes are `World model:`, `Goal model:`, `Action model:`, `Recent findings:`, `Open questions:`, `Plan:`, and `Cross-level notes:`.\nWhen calling `python`, emit exactly the tool-call format shown elsewhere in this prompt for this model. Use only that format; do not add markdown fences, prose wrappers, or alternate tool-call syntax. Do not quote or place tool-call markup inside explanatory text; when you decide to call the tool, emit the tool call itself.\nIf you use MOUSE, include integer row and col arguments.\nEFFICIENCY BUDGET \u2014 your score on each level is (baseline_actions / your_actions)^2, so every wasted action costs you quadratically.\nLevel 2: you have used 42 of about 58 target actions so far.", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "THINKING", "content": "After UPx2, LEFTx2, SPACE:\n- Before SPACE: left red (16-19, 8-11), blue (16-19, 12-31), right red (24-27, 24-35)\n  - The left red shrunk from (16-19, 8-19) to (16-19, 8-11) when the blue moved to overlap with it.\n  - A new right red appeared at (24-27, 24-35)!\n- After SPACE: left red (16-19, 8-31), blue (24-24, 24-35)\n  - The left red expanded from (16-19, 8-11) to (16-19, 8-31).\n  - The blue moved from (16-19, 12-31) to (24-27, 24-35).\n  - The right red at (24-27, 24-35) disappeared (or was replaced by the blue).\nSo the pattern is:\n1. Moving the blue to overlap with a red block causes the red block to shrink.\n2. SPACE causes the red block to expand and the blue to jump to another red block position.\nCurrently:\n- Left red: (16-19, 8-31)\n- Blue: (24-27, 24-35)\nThe left red is now 24 cols wide (8-31). The blue is at (24-27, 24-35), which is 12 cols wide.\nI need to figure out how to make the left red disappear. Let me try moving the blue to overlap with the left red and pressing SPACE again.\nTo move the blue to the left red position:\n- UP 2: 24-27 -> 20-23 -> 16-19\n- The blue is at cols 24-35, and the left red is at cols 8-31. They over